<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-03-27a.92.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100559" speakername="Lord Sainsbury of Turville" colon=":" colnum="92"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199900/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60327w01.htm#60327w01_spnew3">
	<p pid="a.92.2/1">We envisage that the main bulk of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease claims will be settled by 2009. However, the department remains unable to set firm end dates for the COPD scheme due to the number of current unknowns and uncertainties surrounding the scheme. These are being considered in court.</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/2">The estimated total costs to be incurred, as categorised above, are:</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/3">(a) &pound;590 million <sup>1</sup> for administrative costs, including claims handling and consultancy,</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/4">&pound;357 million for medical costs and &pound;50 million for records management;</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/5">(b) &pound;1196 million;</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/6">(c) &pound;44 million;</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/7">(d) around &pound;12 million; and</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/8">(e) &pound;2,451 million.</p>
	<p pid="a.92.2/9" class="indent"><sup>1</sup> Claim handling, records management and defendants' legal costs cannot be broken down. These figures represent the total estimate for both schemes.</p>
</reply>
